    "Unlike fields with abundant labeled data (e.g., biomedical science), paleontology often deals with a limited number of suitably preserved fossil specimens (Hoyal Cuthill et al. 2020).",
    "Although potential training datasets do exist (Hendricks et al. 2015), they are insufficient considering 1 3 the large volumes of data necessary for practical DL training.",
    "Additional challenges arise from the sheer number of organisms encountered in paleontology, and in the case of volume image datasets, the lack of any standardised format with which to record segmented regions within tomographic data.",
    "While neontologists focus on extant fauna, paleontologists must contend with a vast expanse of geological time, characterized by uneven and strongly biased sampling (Dunhill et al. 2018).",
    "Thus, the fossil record represents only a fraction of the organisms that have ever lived on Earth."
